            <p:rationale>Hardening ensures that unnecessary functions no longer exist, avoiding unnecessary security risks. The security of components that protect IT systems is particularly important and, therefore, at the very least these components must be hardened. </p:rationale>
            <p:implications>Unnecessary and unused features of infrastructural components that play a role in the security of other systems such as directory servers, proxies, and authentication and login systems are turned off. Manageability of these components has been closed as much as possible. Encrypted management mechanisms are used, and control is only allowed from predefined IP addresses. Any unused protocols, services and network ports are disabled. For access to the switches, use is made of Virtual LAN (VLAN) systems.</p:implications>
